2. We may obſerve the perſon addreſt to; 
               viz. 
               John the Baptiſt, for that is the antecedent to the Relative him in our Text: which intimates to us, that Chriſt's Ambaſſadors are proper perſons to be conſulted with, about matter of duty, by perſons of all orders and degrees. The Prieſt's lips muſt preſerve knowledge; and we are to aſk the Law at his mouth.
